Description: Ostracon, fragment of the shoulder section of a drab-coloured pottery wine-jar, interior slightly grooved, exterior covered with a light-brown slip and with remains of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393093) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393093)
Associated places: Named in inscription: House of Aten
